cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on fault-tolerant distributed systems, which is a key area of research in this sub-category. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with the development of specialized fault-tolerant communication primitives, which is a key area of research in this sub-category. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with Byzantine behavior, which is a type of security threat in distributed systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the development of protocols for reliable communication in distributed systems, which is a key area of research in this sub-category. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication protocols in distributed systems, which is a key area of research in this sub-category.
